@houshengbo  - I see you are removing the tests/src/packages/SamplesTests.java file from openwhisk and I assume moving to openwhisk-catalog.  How are you handling test utility dependencies in this file such as the following:

import common.Pair;
import common.TestUtils;
import common.WskCli;

@csantanapr , it seems I can't generate encryption key for this repo, so could you please help take a look when you available? Thanks a lot.

Just FYI, in my own local fork the CI test passed, I attached the raw log.
[log.txt](https://github.com/openwhisk/openwhisk/files/370562/log.txt)

@rabbah brings up an important point but I think there are actually two issues.  I agree on (2) and in-between on (1).
1.  Should the action be failed if it exceeds the quota?  I am ambivalent with it failing so the user is alerted in some way.  Alternatives are to consider error codes that signify something unusual has happened but not a failure.  We may need this anyway to alert the user that the action required a retry.
2. Should the log be truncated if it exceeds the quota?  I would argue no for two reasons.  First, they are allowed to use space up to the quota so why would we impose a severe penalty for going a little over  and not just allow them to have the log up to the quota?  Second, turning the entire log into the string `log limit exceeded` would leave no clues in the log about why the log became so voluminous.
